						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in front of the Hanuman temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">10th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It refers to the rule of a feudatory of Sāntaḷige-nāḍu a subdivision of Banavāsi-nāḍu and records a grant of 50 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of land in Saravaḍigi, income from Sunday [Tax] collection and 5 house sites by the palace servant Neṟayaṇṇa of Sāntalige-nāḍu. Bankāpura is mentioned in this record.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 10th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
